result.execSummary:
The defendant Darius M. Kinney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(b).
  • Armed Robbery with Threat of Force [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court set $165.00 JOINT/SEVERAL with co-actors charge and sentenced for these offenses; payable to Jamie S.

BOTH COUNTS: Provide a DNA sample; pay the related surcharges. Pay court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments including the restitution surcharge are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid during term of ES; non-payment penalty shall be a civil judgment.

Concurrent with Count 2 and Consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 144 days time served. 


Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program after serving the first 2 years of sentence and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program
